	<br><br><br>	<br><br><br><div id="tab2" class="tab-content"><d><center>History; </center></d> <br> 
Far in the frozen north, where the winds howl like wolves and snow blankets the world in silence, stands the hidden temple of the Iskald Varder. It is a place of austere beauty and relentless trials, where the unyielding are forged into living weapons. Taken as an infant, a desperate offering from a struggling settlement clinging to life at the edge of the icy wilds, Jozif was thrust into this unforgiving order. He was made to endure grueling trials and bitter winters alone, exposed to the merciless elements and forced to wrest survival from the frozen earth. These ordeals, meant to purge weakness, shaped him into a relentless survivor.

He emerged bearing the Blodmerke—Frostskinn, Stormbryter, and Tordenklo—each a testament to his remarkable endurance and the beginning of his bond with Morozith, the shadowy god of frost and secrets. These sacred marks, etched with the power of his trials, sharpened his natural abilities, turning him into a weapon of silent precision. Yet, the later branding of the Asuraskja during a mission against a rogue sorcerer shattered his fragile balance. The cursed mark made him a beacon for eldritch forces, altering his fate forever and binding him to a path of endless strife. Now he treads a shadowed path, fighting not only the foes of his order but the creeping darkness within, a stark reminder of the cost of survival in the frostbitten wilds.
</div>

<div id="tab5" class="tab-content">  <br><br><br><br><center>Abilities; <br><br></center>

<li>Frostjern Discipline: This ruthless martial art, perfected by the Iskald Varder, uses Jozif’s formidable strength and precision to deadly effect, making his body a weapon honed by ice and shadow. He favors unarmed combat as a pure expression of his devotion to Morozith but is equally skilled with weapons when the need arises.<br><br>

<li>Blodmerke Activation: Through intense meditation or the spilling of his own blood, Jozif can temporarily heighten his physical abilities by drawing on the power of the Blodmerke. However, each activation, particularly when fueled by blood, deepens the influence of the Asuraskja, creating a dangerous dependency.<br><br>

<li>Physical Attributes: Years of brutal training and the blessings of the Blodmerke have endowed him with strength, agility, and endurance far beyond the limits of ordinary men.<br><br>

<li>Silent Grace: The Frostskinn Mark and rigorous discipline allow him to move with an uncanny silence, his steps as soft as falling snow despite his size.<br><br>

<li>Heightened Instincts: His senses are sharpened to near-superhuman levels, allowing him to detect faint changes in his surroundings, foresee danger, and hunt his prey with almost supernatural accuracy. This instinct is crucial in his battle against the constant threat of eldritch entities.<br><br>

<li>Cold Immunity and Poison Resilience: A lifetime spent enduring frost and sacred trials has rendered him immune to the bite of the cold and granted him an exceptional ability to neutralize toxins within his body.<br>
</div>
<br><br><br><br>
<div id="tab6" class="tab-content"> <center>Appearances </center><br> <br> Jozif is an imposing figure, his large frame and thick bones supporting a lean, powerfully muscled physique. Pale skin, a testament to the harsh northern climate and the strain of his curse, stretches taut over his athletic build. Dark, untamed hair frames a face etched with sharp angles and unwavering stoicism. His heterochromatic eyes, one crimson, the other a chilling silver-blue, add to his unsettling presence. He favors dark, functional clothing, blending seamlessly with the shadows. </div>
 

